cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC

This paper involves natural language processing techniques to analyze tweets related to stress and relaxation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the study involves infodemiology, which is the study of information and communication patterns in populations, suggesting a possible fit with cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The study also involves analyzing data from different cities, which could fit with cs.SD (Software Engineering and Systems Development). The study also involves analyzing data related to health, which could fit with cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks).
